  "market_context": "Uptrend on Gold 30-min chart with clear higher highs and higher lows. A major support zone around 2151.000 had been tested multiple times, accumulating retail long stop-losses below it.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept liquidity below the key support level (2151.000), triggering retail stops, then reversed sharply upward into a pre-identified Fair Value Gap (FVG) demand zone on the left side of the chart.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a clear uptrend with repeated rejection at a key support level (~2151.000), indicating accumulated long stop-losses below it (SSL).",
    "Step 2: Noted that smart money aims to sweep retail stop-losses before reversing, so entry should occur after the sweep is confirmed.",
    "Step 3: Looked left on the chart to identify a Fair Value Gap (FVG) as an extreme demand zone — the primary Point of Interest for long entries.",
    "Step 4: Observed price breaking below support (liquidity sweep), then reversing with strong bullish momentum toward the FVG zone.",
    "Step 5: Concluded the setup combines market structure (support level) and liquidity (sweep below it) to confirm a high-probability long opportunity."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Always look left for imbalances (e.g., FVGs) when identifying liquidity sweeps; the sweep itself is not the trade — the reversal into a prior demand zone is the valid entry trigger.",
